 is also responsible for its antiseptic and expectorant properties.", "constituents": [], "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Pellaea falcata are flavonoids, tannins, and phenolic acids, which have been identified due to their antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. The flavonoids present in Pellaea falcata, such as quercetin and kaempferol, have been found to exhibit antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory activities, contributing to its healing properties. Tannins in Pellaea falcata have been reported to possess astringent and antiseptic properties, while phenolic acids like caffeic and ferulic acid have been found to exhibit antimicrobial and antioxidant activities. The presence of these compounds in Pellaea falcata suggests its potential use in wound healing and skin conditions due to its ability to reduce inflammation and prevent infections. The antioxidant properties of these constituents may also contribute to the plant's ability to protect against cell damage and promote overall health.", "herb_names_common": [], "preparations": [{"name": "infusion", "mentions": 19, "confidence_score": 149, "total_score": 2831}, {"name": "tincture", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 132, "total_score": 2640}, {"name": "tea", "mentions": 16, "confidence_score": 131, "total_score": 2096}, {"name": "salve", "mentions": 20, "confidence_score": 86, "total_score": 1720}, {"name": "decoction", "mentions": 11, "confidence_score": 60, "total_score": 660}, {"name": "ointment", "mentions": 8, "confidence_score": 28, "total_score": 224}, {"name": "infused oil", "mentions": 3, "confidence_score": 20, "total_score": 60}, {"name": "pellaea tea", "mentions": 2, "confidence_score": 19, "total_score": 38}, {"name": "poultice", "mentions": 5, "confidence_score": 15, "total_score": 75}, {"name": "capsule", "mentions": 1, "confidence_score": 3, "total_score": 3}, {"name": "vaporizer", "mentions": 1, "confidence_score": 2, "total_score": 2}, {"name": "infus